<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="24" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="24">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="24">
Because of the characteristics of thallus and lirellae, this species belongs to 
<taxonomicName class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Graphidaceae" genus="Graphis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Graphis" order="Ostropales" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Graphis</taxonomicName>
and is here recombined as 
<taxonomicName genus="G." lsidName="G. lecanactiformis." pageId="11" pageNumber="24" rank="species" species="lecanactiformis.">G. lecanactiformis.</taxonomicName>
It is similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Graphidaceae" genus="Graphis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Graphis tenuirima" order="Ostropales" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tenuirima">Graphis tenuirima</taxonomicName>
(Shirley) A.W. Archer in anatomy, but differs in ascoma morphology (dussii morph according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Luecking, R" journalOrPublisher="Lichenologist" pageId="15" pageNumber="28" pagination="363 - 452" title="A world-wide key to the genus Graphis (Ostropales: Graphidaceae)." url="http://dx.doi.org/10.1017/S0024282909008305" volume="41" year="2009">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lücking">Luecking</normalizedToken>
et al. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
) and the larger ascospores. In the world key to 
<taxonomicName class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Graphidaceae" genus="Graphis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Graphis" order="Ostropales" pageId="11" pageNumber="24" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Graphis</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Luecking, R" journalOrPublisher="Lichenologist" pageId="15" pageNumber="28" pagination="363 - 452" title="A world-wide key to the genus Graphis (Ostropales: Graphidaceae)." url="http://dx.doi.org/10.1017/S0024282909008305" volume="41" year="2009">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lücking">Luecking</normalizedToken>
et al. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
), this species would key out at couplet 23 in Group 5.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
